PythonC++ <pre><code>RobotClient(addr="192.168.5.2:50051")
</code></pre> <pre><code>Client(addr="192.168.5.2:50051")
</code></pre> Parameter Type Default Description <code>addr</code> string <code>"192.168.5.2:50051"</code> gRPC service address <p>Constructor Behavior:</p> <ol> <li>Opens gRPC channel to <code>addr</code>.</li> <li>Queries current speed ratio via <code>get_state()</code> and stores locally.</li> <li>Enables obstacle avoidance (<code>set_obstacle_avoidance(true)</code>) and stores result locally.</li> </ol> PythonC++ <pre><code># Context manager (recommended)
with RobotClient("192.168.5.2:50051") as robot:
    robot.balance_stand()
# Channel auto-closes on exit
</code></pre> <pre><code>robot::Client client("192.168.5.2:50051");
client.balance_stand();
// Auto-cleanup on destruction
</code></pre>

PythonC++ <pre><code>robot = RobotClient("192.168.5.2:50051")
state = robot.get_current_state_name()
print(f"Current state: {state}")
</code></pre> <pre><code>robot::Client client("192.168.5.2:50051");
auto state = client.get_current_state_name();
std::cout &lt;&lt; "Current state: " &lt;&lt; state &lt;&lt; std::endl;
</code></pre>

